            "id": "9d8d99b129854fcdb613d",
            "questionText": "A high-speed train embarks on a journey consisting of three distinct phases. Initially, it accelerates uniformly from rest for $!$20$!$ seconds, reaching a speed of $!$30 \\ m/s$!$. Following this, it maintains a constant velocity of $!$30 \\ m/s$!$ for a period of $!$60$!$ seconds. Finally, as it approaches the next station, it undergoes uniform deceleration, coming to a complete stop in $!$10$!$ seconds. Calculate the total distance travelled by the train throughout its entire journey.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "82026afaa7d34691b11d7",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the acceleration during the first phase. To do so, identify the appropriate SUVAT equation that links the initial speed, final speed, time, and acceleration.",
