            "questionText": "A cannon is positioned at the edge of a cliff, $!$100 \\text{ meters}$!$ above sea level. It fires a cannonball horizontally with an initial speed of $!$50 \\text{ m/s}$!$. Neglecting air resistance and using $!$g = 9.8 \\text{ m/s}^2$!$ for the acceleration due to gravity, calculate the horizontal distance from the base of the cliff that the cannonball travels before hitting the water below.",
